It's hard to know if this is a bug or not, but it was certainly unexpected for me. Also, it makes things more complicated than they should be since you have to maintain your own state (list of panes) instead of relying on `PaneContainer::getPanes()`.
### Steps to Reproduce

``` js
atom.workspace.paneContainer.onDidAddPane(event => {
  if (atom.workspace.paneContainer.getPanes().indexOf(event.pane) === -1) {
    throw new Error("That's weird.");
  }
});
```

Then split a pane.

**Expected behavior:** No error. (The pane has been added when the did-add-pane event is emitted.)

**Actual behavior:** Error
### Versions

Atom 1.10
El Capitan 10.11.6
